title._content: The Crest of Thompson Pass (Elevation 2,771 Feet). Here the Richardson Highway Winds through Rocky Benches That Seem to Steer the Road Toward the Deserted Glacier, Eight Miles and an Entire Valley Away to the South. Mile 760, near the Alaska Pipeline Rout
